The instance metadata service.

Code running on an instance can query a special link-local address to learn facts about itself: its instance identifier, its zone, its attached role's credentials, its tags, its user data, and its addresses.

There are two versions, and the difference is security. Version one is a simple request with no authentication, which makes it vulnerable to server-side request forgery: a bug in your app that fetches an attacker-controlled url can be tricked into leaking the role's credentials. Version two requires you to first request a session token and then present it on every read, which binds the token to the instance and defeats that attack.

New launches default to requiring version two. Treat version one as deprecated; it has been the single biggest cause of credential-theft incidents on ee-see-two.
